<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 4:28PM EDT  by NWS Wakefield</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL AFFECT NORTH CENTRAL GREENSVILLE...
NOTTOWAY...CENTRAL DINWIDDIE AND NORTHEASTERN BRUNSWICK COUNTIES...
At 428 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located over Nottoway, or
near Blackstone, moving southeast at 30 mph.
Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail are possible with this
storm.
Locations impacted include...
Dinwiddie, Blackstone, Crewe, McKenney, Nottoway, Burkeville,
Wilsons, Fort Pickett, Dewitt, Spainville, North Wellville, Irby,
Forkland, Wharfs Store, Darvills, Wellville, Dominy Corner,
Fergusonville, Hebron and Blackstone Airport.
If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</description>
